dialog{
  id = "CHARA",
  text = [[
 :)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_message",
  text = [[
At last, you're here, dear Visitor.
Finally, these long corridors will
serve their purpose...
What is this place ?
Who am I ?
Why do you look like that ?
So many questions...
Answers you'll find
within these walls...
Climb the stairs before you
and join me without delay.
I'm waiting for you, dear Player.
By the way, if you want to
customize the game controls,
press F1 on your keyboard.
Due to numerous issues with
the 'Menu of Doom', I decided to
remove that button from the joypad.
There. I didn't know where else
to put this dialogue...
Now hurry up !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.billy",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hey, did you know that the house
northwest of the Citadel has been
abandoned for years ?
They say that bandits have even
set up a hideout there... There's
an entrance at the top of the house
Isn't that a fascinating story ?
You should check it out sometime...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.billy_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Uhh...$0 Hi...$0 What what ? ?$0
I'm not doing anything shady...$0
Just hanging around, that's all.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.granny",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2My husband is so devoted
to the Ancients who made
Hyrule prosper,
he goes every day to
pay his respects at their tomb,
located in the Northwest Plains.
It's an important act of memory
for him. He only comes home
at night to sleep, then
leaves again at sunrise.
I find this love and passion
admirable, but... If only he cared
as much about his dear
and loving wife...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.old_man_grave_day",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2I'm paying my respects at the tomb
of the Ancients of the Kingdom...
We must continue to honor them.
Did you know they fought
to the death for the
prosperity of the Hylian people ?
This tomb was built so
their service to the homeland
would never be forgotten !
So please let me pray,
thank you.$0
Darned disrespectful youth...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.old_man_grave_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2Zzzz... All for the memory of
the Ancients... Darned kids
don't respect anything anymore...
Zzzz...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.old_man_grave_twilight",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2Oh dear, where is
that blasted bridge...
I don't have my glasses.
Here ? Oh no... This way ? Nope.
What ? Who are you ? Leave me be !$0
Darned disrespectful kids...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.running_kid",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Yayyyyy ! Run run run
run run run...
RUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUN !
(uhh okay... What did you expect
trying to talk to a kid
sprinting at full speed...)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.seaten_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
What's that ? My wife runs the inn
and my son is playing outside.
Can't wait for tonight when I get
to see them again. There's nothing
like being with your family !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.seaten_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
How wonderful it is to be here
every evening with
my son and my wife.
I'm not looking forward to
going home... Another day
alone... What a life.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.weird_guy",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello there, little one.
Have you tried the food
at the inn ?
It's not as good
as it used to be...
Such a shame...
Since the innkeeper ran out
of Sugar Flakes, it's
just not the same !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.weird_guy_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Good evening, little one.
Isn't the night beautiful tonight ?
I like walking through
the alleys at night, there's
nothing suspicious about that...
Right ?
Heard that before, have you ?$0
You're a funny one !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.field.zelda",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome, Link, Hero
chosen by the Goddesses.
I am Princess Zelda.
But you knew that already,
didn't you ?
You also know your destiny
is probably to find some
lost legendary artifacts
in 3 hidden Temples...
And blah blah blah, you're
Hyrule's only hope, and blah blah
blah you have to hurry...
Even though we all know that
Ganon is just going to wait
until you gather all the artifacts
so he can steal them at the end
of the game and take over Hyrule...
Then you'll get the Master Sword,
same one as always,
to finally go beat that nasty-$0
Oh...$0
What's happening to me ?
I felt like this whole story
was just a video game !
But... what's a video game ?
I don't know !
I'm just a fragile Princess...
Save us, Link !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.ganon",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Well well, look who it is...
Mister "Hero" himself.
Welcome to my Castle.
Do you really hope to defeat me
with that pathetic sword ?
Don't be foolish !
I will destroy you, right here.
And once I find the Triforce,
the World shall be mine !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.ganon_alt",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Ah ah ah ah !
The Triforce is finally mine !
I must thank you, Link.
I've been searching for those
Pendants for years !
What ?$0 I'm dumb ??$0
Insolent brat !
Taste the Power of the
Sacred Triangles !
Be destroyed, right here !
That is my will, Triforce !
AND LET THE WORLD BE MINE !!!
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_allclear",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You've reached the top rank,
dear VIP Member. Congratulations !
Our Great Manager awaits you...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_bronze_next",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Earn 10 Fidelity Points
to reach the Bronze Rank.
Good luck.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_give",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome, good Sir.
Welcome to the Great Shop,
the ideal place for all your needs!
Here, our Customers enjoy a
unique Fidelity Program
rewarding every purchase !
Allow me to give you our
Fidelity Card. With every purchase
at the Great Shop, you'll earn
Fidelity Points.
Gather enough Points and come
see me again.
Your Fidelity Rank will increase,
granting you access to new
Shop Sections and more
purchase options !
We have some truly rare items
in stock.
Don't hesitate ! Shop here and be
rewarded for your fidelity, Sir.
Here is your Fidelity Card.
Use it wisely.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_give_bronze",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Your purchases have earned you
the Bronze Rank of the Great Shop.
As a token of your effort,
here is the Bronze Fidelity Card.
You now have access to the
Bronze Section of the Shop.
Not bad !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_give_gold",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Your purchases have earned you
the Gold Rank of the Great Shop.
As a token of your effort,
here is the Gold Fidelity Card.
You now have access to the
Gold Section of the Shop.
Excellent.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_give_silver",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Your purchases have earned you
the Silver Rank of the Great Shop.
As a token of your effort,
here is the Silver Fidelity Card.
You now have access to the
Silver Section of the Shop.
Well done.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_give_vip",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Your purchases have earned you
the VIP Rank of the Great Shop.
As a token of your effort,
here is the VIP Fidelity Card.
Congratulations.
Dear VIP Member, our
Great Manager awaits you
to deliver your reward.
Do not keep him waiting.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_gold_next",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Earn 50 Fidelity Points
to reach the Gold Rank.
Keep it up.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_npc",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Great Shop,
Sir. If you want to talk business,
go to the other side.
Me ? Well, I've worked here
for 10 years and didn't have
a line of dialogue until I figured
nosy folks like Kakash/Raz
would try talking to me...
Thanks guys.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_silver_next",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Earn 25 Fidelity Points
to reach the Silver Rank.
Best of luck.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.card_employee_card_vip_next",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Earn 99 Fidelity Points
to reach the VIP Rank.
Just a bit more effort.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.welcome_grade_bronze",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Greetings, young man.
Welcome to the Bronze Section.
Take a look at my wares.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.welcome_grade_gold",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Welcome, my Lord.
Welcome to the Gold Section.
Take a look at my rare items.
Special products just for you,
O Golden Member. You won't find
better quality anywhere ! Slurrp.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.welcome_grade_normal",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Hey.
Welcome to the Standard Section.
Pick whatever you want.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.welcome_grade_silver",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Hello, good Sir.
Welcome to the Silver Section.
Have a look at what I've got.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.hyrule_field.great_shop.welcome_grade_vip",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Welcome, my very dear
VIP Member. Yes, it's me :
Your favorite traveling merchant !
To reward you for your hard-earned
climb through my Shop's ranks,
here's a gift...
Everything in this Section is
dirt cheap - 90% off !
Enjoy it to the fullest, dear VIP.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.bodyguard_intendant",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
I'm the personal bodyguard
of the Lake Village Steward.
Watch your manners !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.bodyguard_sage",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
We are the personal guards
of the Blue Sage.
Speak to him with respect !
Or else...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.drunk_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh hey, you managed to
find me. I like staying
away from everyone...
Want a little tip ?
I suggest you pay attention
to the trees around here.
Some hide secrets in their branches
Others can be followed along their
trunks and lead to well-hidden paths
even if it doesn't look like it...
Details matter !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.drunk_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Aaah, nothing beats a nice glass
of wine at home to unwind at night.
The bar ? Oh no no, I leave such
nonsense to my drunken peers !
I'm better than that.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.2-miroir.answer_no",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
How dare you ?$0
How dare you refuse
this Beauty standing before you ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.2-miroir.answer_yes",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Wonderful ! Now I can admire
myself from every corner
of my home !
Oh yes, take this Broom.
It's brand new !
Perfect for cleaning, right ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.2-miroir.default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
If only I had a Mirror...
I love gazing at myself
all day long !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.2-miroir.done",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Ah, you're back. Thanks again
for that Mirror ! Now I can admire
myself all the time. Hee hee hee !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.2-miroir.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh, is that a Mirror
you've got there ! Perfect timing !
You won't need it, I'm sure...
Would you give it to me ?
With pleasure, beauty !
I'm more handsome, so there !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.3-balai.answer_no",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh... what a shame...
What will I do now ?
Oh, misery...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.3-balai.answer_yes",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Fantastic ! I feel alive again !
How can I reward you ?
I know ! Take this precious Stone :
It's a pure Diamond.
You deserve it ! Go on, take it !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.3-balai.default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh dear... my old Broom is
completely worn out, I can't
clean properly with it.
If I could find a new one,
it would be a miracle !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.3-balai.done",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Yay ! I feel great again !
What about you ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.3-balai.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
That's a brand-new Broom
you've got there ! Would you
give it to me ?
My old Broom is too worn
to clean properly.

Can I have your Broom ?
With pleasure !
No, cleaning awaits me...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.4-pierre.answer_no",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Very well. I suppose
you're not ready yet...

Forgive me for bothering you,
good Sir.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.4-pierre.answer_yes",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh, thank you my friend.
Here's a book I borrowed
from the library.
What will you do with it ?
No idea !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.4-pierre.default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Behold this beautiful book
on Rare Stones.
Fascinating stuff !
I'm actively seeking
rare Minerals.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.4-pierre.done",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
My collection keeps growing
by the day.

But mind you, these are not
just rocks !
They are Minerals !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.4-pierre.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh, you have a Diamond ?
I've just started collecting
Minerals... Would you be
willing to trade it ?


I want that Diamond !
Yes, I don't need it.
No, I'll be RIIICH !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.5-livre.default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Looks like there's a book
missing from this library...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.5-livre.done",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
The book is neatly placed,
and the door is now open.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.5-livre.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You're holding a book
that seems to belong
in the library.
Would you like to place it there ?
Yes
No
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.answer_no",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Very well. You must not be
ready yet... come back when
you are !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.answer_yes",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Very well ! Here is the Key
to the Cave ! Watch out for
the monsters inside, and
good luck with your journey !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Greetings, young one !
Welcome to Lake Village.
I am the Blue Sage.
I assume you're here
in search of a Trophy ?

That artifact lies in the Cave
northwest of the Village...
However, monsters have
been spotted there recently...


I sealed the entrance,
and I can't give the Key
until you prove your worth.
Explore the Village and
seek out a Pearl Necklace.
That will prove you are
worthy of the Key.


Here's a hint : talk to the locals
and solve their problems...
It'll lead you to the Necklace !
Come back once you have it !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.default_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Ah, you're back ! Hmm...
Did you find the Necklace ?
If so, show it to me !
Don't forget to help the villagers-
that will lead you to it !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.done",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Ah, hello again young Hero.
Has there been any progress
in your Quest ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.echange.6-collier.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Ah, you're back ! And I see you
have the Pearl Necklace !
Then I see no reason not to give
you the Lake Cave Key...


Do you want the Key ?
Yes, I want it !
No, I'm scared of monsters...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.intendant",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
What is it ?
I'm the Village Steward.
I'm very busy ! Be gone !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.intendant_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
What is it ?
I'm the Village Steward.
I'm very busy ! Be gone !
What, this glass of wine ?$0
...$0 It's for work !
Move along now.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.kitchen_girl_day",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Aaah what a wonderful day !
I can enjoy it because all today's
meals are already prepared !
The Blue Sage is so happy
to have me as his cook. Everything
is always ready in no time !
And I can relax all day long,
until the next night... What a life
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.kitchen_girl_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Faster ! Faaaster !
I must finish preparing all
the meals for tomorrow !
Quality ? Who cares !
As long as everyone gets
their meals for the day and night,
that's what matters most !
That's just how this world works.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.library_woman",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2Oh misery... These books won't
put themselves away...
And so many are still missing...
Maybe if I noted down who
borrowed what, I could keep up.
Misery...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.library_woman_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$2Good evening, young man.
Are you admiring the starry sky
above Lake Hylia too ?
It's truly magnificent
to look at... What ?$0
Ah yes, you can't see it.
That's such a shame...
If I were you, I'd file
an issue right away.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.mustache_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello there, young man.
Welcome to Lake Village.
A lovely place to live.
Take your time and stroll around
this quiet corner, far from the
hectic Castle Town...

Oh, by the way, there are small
pots all over the place.
If you find them, break them !
They should contain helpful stuff
for your journey. And they refill
over and over ! Awesome.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.mustache_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
There's nothing like a nice drink
at the bar after a whole day
standing still !
And tomorrow, it'll all start
again, endlessly... But hey,
that's what they call 'adding life'
apparently.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.seaten_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello young man.
Need something ?
There's no Trophy here.
But the room in this inn has a
very well-hidden secret !
Have you found the Lens ?
Zeldo the Magnificent overused it
in this new Wave...
Use it everywhere !
You'd be surprised how many
secrets it reveals.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.seaten_man_kill",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello young man.
Need wha...$0 Hey !$0
I recognize you !
You dared to rob me in
the last Wave ! You may have
forgotten, but I haven't !
Want to taste Zeldo's magic
again ?$0 Come on, just once...$0
game:set_life(0)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.seaten_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Good evening young man.
This starry view above the Lake
is beautiful, isn't it ?
Once again, the Great Zeldo
didn't have time to implement it...
He's so lazy, huh ?
If you think that, you don't know
him at all ! Believe me,
Making is his true passion !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.soldier_kitchen",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
These kitchens are so quiet
during the day... But at night,
it's a whole different story !
Come back at night, and
you'll see what I mean...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.soldier_kitchen_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You're just in time, kid !
This is when the kitchen
gets busy ! Look closely...
That woman works so fast
and efficiently she can prep
all the meals in one night.
That way, she's free
all day long...
I find it fascinating.
What ? The food's not fresh
and it's all reheated ? Well,
quality isn't a priority !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.soldier_library",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh man, I'm so boooored...
Who thought it was a good idea
to make me guard this library ?
There's nothing but
old books here!
This job sucks... Ugh.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.soldier_stockroom",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh man, I'm so boooored...
Who thought it was a good idea
to make me guard this storeroom ?
There's nothing but
old trinkets here !
This job sucks... Ugh.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.lake_village.tim",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello there, traveler.
As you can see, my house
is completely flooded !
What ? A system to drain
the water ? Oh no no,
I don't have that here...
But if you've got something
that lets you swim in deep
water, happy swimming !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.link_forest.forest_guide_cant_pass",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Mmmh, I see that
you don't have a
Sword or Shield...
Without at least that equipment,
you'll never find your way
through these Woods.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.link_forest.forest_guide_pass",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You have a Sword
and a Shield ?
In that case, you may pass.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.link_forest.link_uncle",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi Link !
Any progress on
your Quest ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_castle_town",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Hyrule Castle Town (prototype) -

Here is a prototype version of
the Hyrule Castle Town map,
with a lovely editor view.
The Labors version takes most of
it and adds useful buildings
for the area.
The 2016 project version is
closer to the one seen in
Forgotten Legend, but I thought
this one was more primitive
and interesting for
The Labors of Zeldo.
Also, it changes things up from
Forgotten Legend !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_evolution",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

 - Map B4 (2015 - 2018 version) -

Here's an interesting screenshot,
with some explanation.
Yes, you read correctly : 2018.
Although The 1st Solarus Quest
was made around 2015/2016, a
'remake' was considered in 2018,
while I was working on the
'Basic Quest'.
This 2018 version was meant
to be shorter and serve as a
prototype for a 'complete' game,
showcasing the Basic Quest's
possibilities.
A sort of Sample Quest, yes...
But when Zeldo's Challenge
Chapter 2 was released, I already
had a game illustrating all that.
So the 2018 version of 1st Solarus
Quest was quickly dropped.
Still, I managed to make a few
things, which you'll mostly
see in this blue Gallery room.
Let's start with the first map.
On the left is the 2016 version,
seen in the Labors, and on the
right the 2018 version, larger.
In the end, I find the 2015 version
has more charm, like a lot of
things that got remade...
Nostalgia perhaps...
Or my love for sadism ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_map_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Temple of Courage V.2018 -

Here's the full map of the Temple
of Courage from The 1st Solarus
Quest, 2018 version.
The path is the same as in
the 2015 version, but the visuals
are completely redone.
And honestly... I now prefer
the 2015 version !
Good choice for the Labors then.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_map_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Temple of Wisdom V.2018 -

Here is the B1F map of the
Temple of Wisdom from The 1st
Solarus Quest, 2018 version.
Some rooms are different but
the general layout and graphics
are mostly the same.
Still, I chose the 2015 version
for the Labors for one good reason:
The 2018 version was not finished.
And... the 2015 one is more
sadistic, eh eh eh.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_menu_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

 - Inventory Menu (prototype) -

Here's the Inventory menu and
how it evolved over time.
At first, I went with a style
similar to Zelda Solarus DX,
since I've always been good
at copying.
Later, starting from the ALTTP
Pack, I made my own menu style
using the gui_designer.
In the end, both styles looked
nice. The pure ALTTP style
stayed with me for a long time
and even appeared in Zeldo's
Challenge Chapter 1, before
becoming a unified type of
menu in Zeldo 2, TotT,
and the 'Basic Quest'.
(a.k.a. the fragments of
the ZeldoPack)
I could write so many notes
about this evolution...
Maybe in a future Wave ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_menu_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Map Menu (prototype) -

Here is the very first version
of the map menu. Very basic,
simple and effective.
But its design...
If I recall correctly, it was
a surface drawn in the map's
on_draw event.
The map showed the room layout,
the compass showed the boss...
and the Big Key icon was just
brutally pasted on the surface.
Ugly ? I know.
But at the time, the ALTTP Pack
had no map menu !
And... it still doesn't today.
Later on, I reused the map
menu from ROTH Solarus Edition,
which is very good !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_misc_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Miscellaneous Development Notes -

Sometimes I'd add small debug tools
or extra features just for fun,
like cheat codes or secret keys.
These little additions helped me
test parts of the game faster,
but I never planned to include
them in the final versions.

For example, the 'god mode'
was useful during early
playtesting to skip difficult
rooms or bosses quickly.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_misc_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Sound Design Evolution -

Sound effects have always
been important to me.
In the beginning, I used
basic midi tones and simple
waveforms for effects.

As the project grew,
I started composing more
complex sounds using
external tools, importing
samples and layering sounds.

This brought a richer
and more immersive feeling
to the gameplay experience.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_num_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Dungeon and Item List Notes -

Here is a detailed list of
planned dungeons for the 2018
version of the game.

Only the three main dungeons
and Hyrule Castle were planned
to be fully developed at that time,
with some bonus dungeons and
Ganon's Tower as extras.

Many ideas never moved past
the note stage but show the scope
I had envisioned.

Items were also catalogued,
some removed or replaced,
aiming for a compact,
fast-paced gameplay experience.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_num_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Equipment Item Notes -

A detailed numeric list
of all equipment items,
most inherited from 2016's version.

Additional quests and features
were also planned for some items.

These notes show how much
preparation and planning
goes into creating a game.

Forgotten Legend also has
similar lists, full of ideas
waiting to come alive in-game.

Patience is key to see them all !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_overworld",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Overworld Sketch -      

A complete version of
the Overworld from The 1st Solarus
Quest, 2018 version.
The layout of the regions
strongly resembles the 2015
version, and what was shown
in this Content Wave.
Only the White Peaks and
Cursed Lands Zone is missing.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_paper_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Paper Notes : Temple of Courage -

Here is the paper version Map
of the Temple of Courage,
in its prototype version.
You can see that the path
is very different compared to
the final version.
Originally, the dungeon's item
was supposed to be Bombs but
that was ultimately changed.
You also notice that the key item
for this place has an icon similar
to the Kokiri Emerald...
This paper version must be
very old given the
differences noted here...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_paper_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

 - Paper Notes : Temple of Wisdom -

Here is the paper version Map
of the Temple of Wisdom,
showing the path up to the Miniboss
The paper version you see here is
very close to the
final version of the place.
There are also some notes
about the basin system
and the dungeon's bestiary/theme.
The paper has been dampened
over time at the top, making it
hard to read...
But it gives it an
intense authentic charm.
So emotional to see a paper
dating back 10 years !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_paper_3",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

 - Paper Notes : Temple of Power - 

Here is the paper version Map
of the Temple of Power,
in its early floors.
The paper version was surely
still in progress, explaining
the empty rooms.
Despite that, the room layout
was already decided, so only
filling them remained.
There is also a small sketch
on the right showing the logic
of the various temple entrances,
and the floor logic was
already established... Zeldo was
meticulous even in 2015 !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_scan_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

 - Scan 1st Solarus Quest folder -

Here is a small screenshot
of my Solarus folder from back then
All dating from 10 years ago !
You can see the folder for The
1st Solarus Quest, simply called
1ere_quete here.
You can also see various
resources and the tunics,
ZSDX and ROTH Solarus Ed. projects.
There are also hidden folders...
maybe for future Content Waves ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_scan_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Scan of first Lua scripts -

Here is a small screenshot of my
first Lua scripts. Not much
else to say.
I just wanted to show you
what my first scripts looked like.
Not bad ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_screen_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Ingame Screen 1 -       

Link is in the legendary
Temple of Light. Does this place
look familiar ?
It's not a coincidence.
You didn't see it in this
Content Wave, but the location
appears in Zelda Forgotten Legend.
And that's normal. After all,
this is its 'Definitive Edition'.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_screen_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Ingame Screen 2 -       

Link wandering in Cocorico Village,
which I didn't present in this Wave
The Village wasn't at an advanced
enough stage to be presentable.
So here is a screenshot.
I also wanted to show it to you for
a simple reason... Night time.
Yes ! A day/night system was
already planned and done.
Many thanks to Christopho for
his tutorials, which already
enabled miracles back then !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_shop",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Great Shop (2015 version) - 

The prototype version of the
Great Shop. The basics
were already there :
Reception and management of the
Fidelity Card, and the different
sections dedicated to various
Fidelity levels.


It's funny to see that this whole
system was already imagined
so long ago...
Sometimes, I surprise
myself ! What a brilliant mind
Zel...$0 Ok ok I stop.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_status",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

          - 100% Status -         

Here is a screen showing
The 1st Solarus Quest
2018 version menu and max status.
You can clearly see that the menu
style changed to a uniform style
at that time, compared to the 2015
version which was an ALTTP-style
menu with multiple tabs.
This menu contains all
planned items, so feel free
to admire it at your leisure.
Try to match the various
icons to the items listed in
the numeric lists. Have fun.
By the way, I just noticed a
mistake in the menu. There is one
item that is not at max status.
Can you find which one ?
I will offer an EXCLUSIVE
screenshot to those who find it.
Contact me :P
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.dev_title",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Title Screen V.2018 -      

Here is a prototype version
of the title screen of The 1st
Solarus Quest 2018 version.
It only lacks the corresponding
subtitle.
You can see that the logo style
was much cleaner and
resembles the original logo
of Zeldo's Challenge - Chapter 1.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.forest_village",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Forest Village -

Link's adventures bring him
to this village hidden deep
in the Forest.
As usual, the local Sage
must know where to find
the Trophy there...
Difficulty : 6/10
Objective : Inspect the Forest
Tip : The usual order.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.ganon_castle",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Ganon's Castle -

The final point of The 1st Solarus
Quest. A dark Castle
ruled by the vile Ganon.
Be careful, this place
was imagined by the 2015 Zeldo,
a worse version than 2017's.
I let my legendary
sadism run free here, even if
the Zone isn't very big...
Difficulty : 9/10
Objective : Defeat Ganon
Tip : It's the 2015 Zeldo...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.hera_mountain",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Hera Mountain -

After conquering the Forest
and the Lake, Link must go...
to the Mountain. Original...
Cross the Path of Death
and make your way to the
summit of Hera Mountain.
Difficulty : 4/10
Objective : Reach the Temple
Tip : Detours are optional.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.hyrule_castle",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Hyrule Castle -

Link ends up in a cell
after Ganon's assault.
Does this seem familiar ?
Your equipment has been hidden
all over the Castle. Retrieve it
and use it for the Trophy.
Difficulty : 7/10
Objective : Retrieve your items
Tip : Inspect the cells.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.hyrule_field",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Hyrule Field -

Here is the vast Hyrule Field
and its accompanying Citadel,
just for you !
Have fun exploring this space
and finding many secrets.
Rubies are very important !
They will serve you in the Great
Shop, an original 2016 idea
that I brought back.
Become a loyal Member of
this money-smelling place
and the Trophy will be yours !
Difficulty : 7/10
Objective : Become a Gold Member
Tip : Long live CAPITALISM !!!
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.kokiri_garden",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Kokiri Garden -

Explore this Forgotten Legend
Dungeon as a preview !

Difficulty : ?/10
Objective : ??
Tip : ???
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.lake_village",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Lake Village -

Link finds himself in this village
by Lake Hylia.
A pleasant place to live !
The Trophy must be somewhere...
Question the local Sage...

Difficulty : 5/10
Objective : Help the inhabitants
Tip : Night time is useless.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.link_house",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Departure Grounds -      

Link lives the start of his great
adventure in this
complete tutorial Zone.
Explore, venture into
the Forest, and find the Temple
of Courage, your goal.
Difficulty : 2/10
Objective : Finish the Temple
Tip : It's the tutorial ! GLHF !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.power_temple",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Temple of Power -

The first draft of the Palace
of Power. Longer, harder,
and less fun !
I recommend activating
Help for Casuals if some parts
seem too tedious.
Difficulty : 8/10
Objective : Finish the Dungeon
Tip : The holes are important.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.1st_solarus_quest.paintings.wisdom_temple",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

     - Temple of Wisdom -

My first water-themed Dungeon !
Will it be as horrible as the
TotT version ? Personally, I find
it less bad...
But you decide !

Difficulty : 7/10
Objective : Finish the Dungeon
Tip : The basins go hand in hand.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.cant_leave",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
It's not the moment
to leave this area...
Let's inspect this place !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.entrance",
  text = [[
Welcome to you Visitor !
Welcome to this somewhat crazy
project : The Labors of Zeldo !
The concept is quite simple :
in my long career as
a Creator, I've made many
things. Unfinished projects,
copies of existing projects,
or just simple tests.
The concept of The Labors of
Zeldo is to offer you
to explore these various Labors,
updated and reworked to be
perfectly playable.
Which brings us to the present
situation. Here you are in front
of me, you, Player of this
crazy project.
I created this magical place
especially to house
my Labors.
Each floor of this Manor
represents a Wave of
content.
You're on the 2nd Floor, which is
therefore about Zelda Tower of the
Triforce, a project from 2017.
As this is the very first floor
of the Manor you're exploring,
let me explain the
functioning of the place to you...
Follow me please. I don't have
much time.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.bar_dude",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hey. You want a drink ? Between
you and me, I think this bar
is actually quite nicely decorated.
But the shop in the back
and the inn room are
terribly empty...
As if they didn't have time
to add furniture...
Kinda funny, isn't it ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.cant_enter_house",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh hey. You wanted to see
what's inside my house, huh ?
That won't be possible, sorry.
You see, the inside of this
house was never mapped.
Too bad.
And I'm just here to stop
you from going in.
Pretty sad, huh...
But hey, you could try
getting into the Traveling
Merchant's house...
You know, the one who had the
Wooden Key... Try hugging the
trees. Trust me.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.dania",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi Link !
I'm Dania, remember me ?
Sure you do, you're going to save
my cousin who got kidnapped by
monsters in Forgotten Legend.
Don't forget it.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.elma",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi Link !
I'm Elma, remember me ?
Sure you do, you're going to save
me from terrible monsters in
Forgotten Legend !
Don't forget me.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.guide",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Greetings, young man.
You're not from around here,
am I right ?
My name is Fado, and I
know everything there is
to know about this Village.
Don't hesitate to ask
if you need anything.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.guide_repeat",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Greetings, young man.
You're not from around here,
am I right ?
My name is Fado, and I
know everything there is
to know about this Village.
Don't hesitate to ask
if you need anything.

...$0What ?$0
You expected a different dialogue ?
How amusing !
Unfortunately, the Great Zeldo
only gave me this one to say.$0
...$0Mmmh ?
Where do you need to go, and what
do you have to do ?$0 Figure it out.
These post-2000 kids, I swear...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.lumberjack",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh hey. Need something ?
My brother went off to the inn
again for the day...
Spending all his time drinking
won't clear the path
back to the house.
Seriously... What a {{{{{
And I thought he had memory lapses
back then...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.mido_day",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh, a stranger... What do you want?
I, the Great Mido, have no time
to waste with you. Get out of here!
Oh and... Be careful.
People around here don't like
outsiders, so watch your manners !
(That's weird... He looks
familiar... Mmmh no,
that's impossible)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.mido_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
What do you want ? I,
the Great Mido, have every right
to relax outside, don't I ?
It's nighttime ? So what ?
Scram, stranger !

(That's weird... He looks
familiar... Mmmh no,
that's impossible)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.saria_quest.chief_after_save",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Thanks again, traveler. You have
my eternal gratitude.
I'm granting you access to our
Altar. Go through the door on the
right, and venture into the Lost
Woods. Follow the idols and find
the path. Good luck with your
search, traveler. You don't seem to
lack courage, I believe in you !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.saria_quest.chief_default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome, traveler.
I'm the Chief of the Forest Village
but also the Green Sage.
Unfortunately, I'm not in the
right state of mind to hear your
request. My daughter, Saria, has
disappeared ! She must've been
kidnapped by Bokoblins, monsters
from deep within the Forest.
Those miserable vermin must be
hiding somewhere, but our
searches have come up empty !
Oh what am I to do...
My dear daughter...
She must be out there, somewhere...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.saria_quest.chief_saria_saved",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Traveler, thank you a thousand
times for saving my sweet Saria.
We are grateful to you.
Thanks also for driving out
those vile Bokoblins from the
Village. We won't be seeing them
again anytime soon !
How can I ever repay you ?$0
A Trophy ?$0
I don't know what you mean.
But if it helps you in your search,
I can grant you access
to our Sacred Altar.
Go through the door on the right,
and venture into the Lost Woods.
Follow the Idols and find the path.
Good luck with your search,
traveler. You don't seem to
lack courage, I believe in you !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.saria_quest.saria_saved",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Thanks again for saving me,
brave traveler.
What's your name ?
Link ?$0
I'll try not to forget it !$0
Good luck on your Quest, Link.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forest_village.saria_quest.save",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You saved my life !
Let's get out of here quickly !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Paper notes : Palace of Wisdom -

The first drafts of what was going
to be the Palace of Wisdom.
The basements are complete.
The ingame version of the Dungeon
is almost identical. Shows that
the first draft is sometimes
the right one !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.10",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

    - Digital notes : Script -    

The most precious notes screenshot
for some : the Script of
Forgotten Legend.
The Script in this form exists
for a large part of the game.
The end is still in my head,
but I know exactly where
I'm going with the storyline.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.11",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Overworld : Hyrule Castle -   

I couldn't resist the urge
to share some maps
in large format !
Here, for example, is the majestic
Hyrule Castle. Is it quite
similar to the one in ALTTP ?
It's just inspiration, I'm
allowed to reuse a castle
shape without criticism, right ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.12",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Overworld : Hera Mountain -   

Another map in large format.
I wanted to share with you the
Hera Mountain, which I find
very beautiful. It's still one
of my best outdoor maps, with
all these nightmare cliffs.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.13",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Complete Overworld (beta) -   

Tradition requires it, here's a
complete version of the
Overworld after the beta.
There's more content in the
current game, but all of that,
I'll let you discover it.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.14",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

     - Ingame screenshot 1 -      

A little screenshot of more
advanced content. The room
decoration might change.
DarkDavy15 has some beautiful
'organic' tiles. Maybe I'll
STEAL some from him...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.15",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

     - Ingame screenshot 2 -      

Another screenshot of more
advanced development that some
of you may have already seen.
Here's how we map a pyramid,
without embellishing the
tiles, it's really dreamlike...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.16",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Game logo and final word -   

Here's the current logo of the
game, as seen in the trailer or
on Itch.
I hope this development gallery
was enjoyable for you.
I made it in 3 days.
We'll meet again in 2025
for updates on Forgotten !
Time to continue the development !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

- Paper notes : Palace of Power -

A paper version of the Graph and
the Map of the Palace of Power.
This one is more 'neat'.
Originally, the Dungeon only had
2 floors. But a basement
was added to extend it.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.3",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Paper notes : South Plain -   

Once again, let me share with you
sketches of the Overworld.

They are usually very rough
and show the general terrain.
The details come while mapping !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.4",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Palace of Courage : Graph -   

I recently discovered a great tool
that allows me to make Graphs
in digital format.
Here is the Graph of the first
Dungeon in the game, all neat,
all clean, all digital !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.5",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Palace of Courage : Map -    

You surely remember my tutorial
on Dungeon design.

Once the Graph is done, we move
on to the Map. Just like the Graph
here it is in digital form !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.6",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Various Graphs -        

The Graphs of the Palace of
Wisdom and Power.
Notice how the Wisdom one is wide
and the Power one is fine.
This reflects their very
different paths and level design.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.7",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Plan : Goriyas' Hideout -    

This mini digital sketch shows
an early draft of the Goriyas'
hideout. It's important to note
that each room is designed to have
a function, making the place feel
realistic.
Beyond being a mini Dungeon,
I wanted the place to feel like a
real home for these monsters.
Hyrule Castle gets the same
treatment. I find this important,
and consistent.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.8",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Digital notes : Bestiary -   

I have A LOT of various notes
on many aspects of Forgotten
Legend.
Here is a screenshot, for example,
showing a part of the Bestiary.
It's filled with info and stats.
Enough to create a real
Tendo figurine gallery !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.forgotten_corridor.paintings.9",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Digital notes : Characters -  

The notes continue with this
entry dedicated to the
game's characters.
I think it's important for them
to have a name, a life, a story...
They are not just random NPCs.
They are characters who can
be endearing, each in their
own way, to infuse the game
with a SOUL.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.rules",
  text = [[
Welcome to the 1st Wave
as such. I hope
you like the music and decor.
They come directly from Tower
of the Triforce.
Hold on, let me explain !
You are currently in the HUB
of the floor. It is always modeled
according to the current Wave.
(Here for example it's the Casino
of Hyrule, an additional Dungeon
planned in Zelda TotT).
From here, you can access
the various Labors I have to offer
and the Galleries.
The right part is dedicated to
the Labors as such. Explore
the various available portals.
Behind each portal is
a painting. Don't hesitate to
consult it for information.
Each portal represents a
Labor Zone. Each Zone
has a Trophy.
By collecting Trophies, new
portals will appear,
and so on until you obtain
the Gold Key, which will allow you
to open the door behind me.
Once through this door, you will
have completed the Wave of
content. Of course, there are
various collectibles to gather.
But I'll let you discover all of
that... why not try for
a 100% ? Good luck anyway...
There's also a Shop. You'll find
various bonuses to help you
in the Labor Zones.
The left part contains
the Development Galleries.
It's basically Bonus content.
However, you'll need to collect
various colored Keys to
access the various sections.
Each Room contains a
different content. I hope
you'll have fun visiting them.
That's all for the explanations.
Congratulations for not falling
asleep while reading them.
This dialogue is way
too long. I have to go.
See you at the end of the floor.
Have fun !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.bed_woman",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi traveler. Welcome to
my humble abode.

I sold my bed to
pay for this magnificent
blonde dye !
So, I take advantage of the night
to go out and admire the stars.
That's the Abuda mentality !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.bed_woman_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
The stars are once again
magnificent tonight...
Look at those colors !
Nothing like the monotonous sky
you can see
over the lands of Hyrule.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.boy",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
They say there's nothing but
ancient ruins
north of the archipelago...
I'd love to visit them...
There must be treasures galore !
When I grow up, I'll go there.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.boy_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Timothy is still daydreaming north
of the archipelago...
He spends his days looking at
the ruins in the distance and
imagining treasure hunting there.
Personally, I've outgrown
all these childish things...$0
How about a game of FIFA ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.chief",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to our peaceful
archipelago, my boy. Make
yourself at home.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.drunk_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hic ! Welcome to the archipelago
of Abuda, my boy ! Hic !
There's more than just
butterbeer in the cellar,
Mr. Potter... Hic !
What ? Did I say something ? Hic !
Hic !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.florist",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello there, young man.
Have you seen my magnificent
flowers outside ?
It's my greatest passion !
However, I no longer have a shovel
to continue my plantations...
Oh, misery...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.kitchen_woman",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh no ! What am I going to do ?
I don't have a frying pan
anymore !
How will I prepare
my omelettes for the
customers who come
for breakfast in the morning...
If only I could find one,
it would be a miracle !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.minigame_hookshot",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to my famous
traveler's skill game !
A game will cost you 10 Rupees.
Do you want to pl... $0oh
wait a moment...$0 This mini-game
was never coded by Zeldo the
Magnificent ! It's really sad...
but then what am I here for ?
No idea, I'm just an NPC !
By the way, I think the
block behind me can be pushed...
But don't touch anything !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.minigame_hookshot_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Good evening young man.
This night is once again
bathed in stars.
What a magnificent view,
don't you think ?
What a pity you can't
enjoy it as well.
Zeldo the Magnificent didn't have
time to implement that...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.minigame_hookshot_steal",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hey ! What do you think
you're doing stealing from
honest people like that ? ?
Just because you're in
a video game doesn't mean you can
do whatever you want !
I remember now my role in this
charade ! To punish you for
your actions !
You see, Zeldo the Great
knew you would steal from me...
He's a true Genius !
So he taught me this spell...
Farewell, thief !
game :set_life(0)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.mother",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Oh, a stranger...
Welcome to our archipelago.
The Abuda archipelago has
prospered for generations, far
from all the troubles present
in the lands of Hyrule.
I would ask you not to
bring your problems here.
We don't need them !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.seaten_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to you, young man.
You're not from around here,
evidently... Welcome to Abuda !
A small archipelago off
Hyrule where life is good.
Relax !
The people here are all very
easygoing, you'll see !
Besides, some like to hide
Rupees, which will be found and
kept by those fortunate enough
to find them. Cool, right ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.seaten_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to my home, young man.
Another night to spend alone...

My companion went
to Hyrule to see his cousin and
still hasn't returned.
I find the nights very long
because of that... wouldn't
you like to stay a little ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.sleeping_man",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Zzzz...
Oh, a new face.
Welcome to Abuda... Zzzz...
A masked man came
to leave a hook nearby
here...
He whispered things at
the same time but I didn't
understand anything... too tired...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.sleeping_man_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Zzzz... Zzzz...$0
(He's sleeping peacefully. It's
better to leave him alone.)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.tim_cleared",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello again traveler. Thanks again
for your invaluable help.
Welcome to my home !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.tim_default",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi there traveler.
I'm glad to see you passing by
my place !
As you can see,
my house is completely
flooded ! Oh misery...
Can you help me ? The
mechanism is in the basement.
Equipped as you are, you should
be able to reach it. I would be
very grateful to you !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.tim_give_shard",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You did it, traveler !
All the water is gone !
Many thanks to you !
I don't have much
on me... oh yes I do !
Take this !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.tim_need_hook",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi there traveler.
I'm glad to see you passing by
my place !
As you can see,
my house is completely
flooded ! Oh misery...
Can you help me ? The
mechanism is in the basement.
Unfortunately, you won't be able
to reach it with your current
equipment. An object on the
beach should help you there !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.travel_agency",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome, young traveler.
I hope your stay on the Abuda 
archipelago is going well.
If you want to return to the lands
of Hyrule, unfortunately I don't
have any more tickets on me.
A mysterious masked man
bought them all from me !
It's really unlucky !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.abuda.uncle",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hi Link. Have you found
any new treasures around
here ?
If you have nothing else to do
here, let's hoist the sails !
Adventure calls us !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.ancient_catacomb.boss_end",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$1...$0
Aaargh...$0 Such pain...$0
and relief at the same time...
Thank you, young adventurer,
I am now freed from this
accursed place thanks to you...
I can join my brother in
the Other World, thank you...$0
I can't stay any longer...
Farewell, young man...$0 
Farewell, this world...$0
Aaaaah...$0...$0
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.ancient_catacomb.boss_intro",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Who goes there ? Have you no shame
disturbing the spirit of Dièze,
the greatest composer of Hyrule ?
Indeed, I composed the Nocturne
of Shadow. I still hold
the sheet music since my death.
What ? You wish to make
use of it ? Ah, ha ! Let me laugh !
I think I'll just
kill you for waking me up,
stranger... 

Sharpen your Lens of Truth if you
don't wish to die too
quickly ! En garde !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.ancient_catacomb.final_sign",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
You who desire to delve into the
deepest Shadows, play this melody
and you will reach your goal...
At this point Link was supposed
to obtain the Nocturne of Shadow
but this will not be the case here.
You have completed this Dungeon
and fulfilled your objective.
Here is the Trophy of Victory !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.ancient_catacomb.miniboss_end",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$1...$0
Aaaah, so this is how it all ends
even for one who is dead...
Thank you, young man, for
freeing my soul trapped
in this place like this...
Before I leave, I have
one last request...
I have little time left...
Free my brother from this place,
I beg of you...$0
Save him from his torment...
The Lens of Truth that lies
in this place will help you there...$0
Find my brother...$0 and use
the Lens to defeat him...$0
He should also aid you
in your quest...$0Please...$0...$0
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.ancient_catacomb.miniboss_intro",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Who dares disturb my sleep ? I am
Baimol, one of the composers in
the service of Agahnim.
Are you searching for the Nocturne
of Shadow, the unique key to the
Shadow Temple ?
I'm sorry, but it's my brother
Dièze who knows its secrets...
Too bad for you, you won't
be able to go see him because
I'm going to take care of you now...
Consider this as a
consequence for disturbing
the spirits of the dead...
By the way, don't hope to see
me or harm me in this darkness...
Goodbye !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.billy_waterfall_day",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hey there. You don't seem to be
from around here... I'm Billy,
a camper.
I've decided to set up camp here
for a while... Hylia Wateralls
are truly breathtaking.
At night, you can see
many glowing fragments
around...
If you want, I invite you to sleep
in my tent and come back tonight,
you'll be able to see them.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.billy_waterfall_night",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Hello, traveler.
Observe how magnificent
Hylia Waterfalls are !
You can see small lights around
if you pay attention...
They are said to come from
magical fragments containing
the Power of the Great Fairies.
I've heard that a Great Fairy used
to live around here, but I've never
seen her...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.great_fairy_waterfall.1st_time",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Young man, I thank you.
I am the Great Fairy of Water.
My powers are finally restored !
Let me reward you by
giving you this Trophy.
Well done !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.great_fairy_waterfall.goodbye",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
There you go. Don't hesitate
to use the present fairies as well.
They will heal you.
See you soon, young man, and
good luck with the rest of
your adventure.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.great_fairy_waterfall.not_enough_fragments",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$1Oh...$0 it seems you don't have
enough Fragments...$0
Come back to me when you have
at least 5 so that I can regain
my powers...$0
Please...$0
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.great_fairy_waterfall.offering_question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$1Young man...$0 I welcome you...$0 
...$0
I am a Great Fairy...$0 
unfortunately, my powers
have dwindled...$0
If you bring me 5 Fragments
of Fairy Power, I will regain
my powers and help you...$0

Could you help me ? $0
$3Yes
No
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.great_fairy_waterfall.welcome",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome, Hero.
Let me ease your
troubles and wounds...
]],
}

