dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.ancient_catacomb",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Ancient Catacomb -

Link explores this tomb in search
of the legendary Nocturne of
Shadow.
Don't be fooled by the illusions
of this mysterious place
and find the song pedestal.
Difficulty : 8/10
Objective : Complete the Dungeon
Tip : Beware of appearances.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.archipelago",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

       - Abuda Archipelago -

Link finds himself on this tropical
archipelago during his adventures.
A dream destination !
Explore the area and find
enough Seashells to
exchange them for your goal.
Difficulty : 3/10
Objective : Collect Seashells
Tip : Have fun and explore.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.castle_tower",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Castle Tower (Alpha) -

Link encounters the mysterious
Agahnim for a duel
at the summit !
Defeat your opponent and
free Hyrule from this
dangerous threat.
Difficulty : 9/10
Objective : Defeat the Boss
Tip : Eliminate the clones.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_graph_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Dungeon Design 1 -

Are you curious to see
how a Dungeon is
designed in Zeldo's mind ?
Since he'll never finish his
tutorial on the subject, here's a
quick guide in 2 steps...
The first step is to imagine
the Dungeon Graph.
This is what this table illustrates...
It's basically the skeleton of the
Dungeon. It represents the path
to take, the various obstacles etc.
Here's the Graph of the beloved
Water Temple. Don't understand
anything ? That's normal.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_graph_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

      - Dungeon Design 2 -

Are you curious to see
how a Dungeon is 
designed in Zeldo's mind ?
Since he'll never finish his
tutorial on the subject, here's the
continuation of the quick guide.
The second step is simply to
transpose the Graph onto a Map.
Thus, we imagine the rooms and
we stage the various obstacles
imagined at the beginning.

This Map is generally more
understandable than the Graph
for non-initiates...
We notice here that Zeldo is
so talented that he didn't even
need to finish his Map.
He already knew the design of the
rest of the Dungeon by heart !
He's really amazing, isn't he ?
(You tell me if I'm overdoing it...)


The last logical step is to
transpose the Map thus made
onto your creation software...
It's probably the longest, but
also the most fun ! Come on Max,
make me a beautiful Dungeon !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_misc_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

    - Side Dungeon : Casino -

Here is the plan of the famous Casino
of Hyrule, the side Dungeon from which
this decoration and music come.
The Dungeon was supposed to allow
to replay all the mini-games
in a more difficult version.
We were supposed to obtain the
Bottomless Ruby Wallet there...
allowing to hold up to 9999 Rupees.
The Dungeon even has a shape
of a 6-faced die. Thanks to Vincent
Jouillat for the great idea !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_misc_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

   - Kingdom of Hyrule (complete) -

Here is the most advanced version
of the Kingdom of Hyrule if we
combine all the Overworld maps
made in 2017 and in 2019.
Enough to let you imagine
Link walking around !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_overworld_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Hyrule Sketch 1 -

The first version of Hyrule
imagined as a digital sketch
The Kingdom was originally
smaller and was supposed to have
4 Dungeons, one in each corner.
This version of the Overworld
will evolve during development...
way too much indeed.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_overworld_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Hyrule Sketch 2 -

A much more advanced version
of the Kingdom of Hyrule, and much
closer to its final version.
The number of Dungeons has
doubled and the Overworld now
makes a 5x5 grid vs the original 4x4.
This version of Hyrule is the one
developed in the Labors
of this first Wave.
Enough to make anyone dizzy
who can imagine
this originally planned world !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_paper_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

         - Paper Notes 1 -

Various paper notes.
This sheet illustrates the 8 Dungeons
of the game and their logical order.
We can see that Link had
a certain freedom in the choice
of Dungeons after the introduction...
Mmmh... it's also difficult now to
say the prerequisites of the last<
Dungeons as the lines converge and
mix with each other... what an
incredible brain Zeldo has !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_paper_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

         - Paper Notes 2 -

Various paper notes.
These include a list of
Hyrule Shops on the left and
a list of different purchases to make
during the game on the right.
We notice that the Rupees
were important and
that Link had to find a lot
of money to complete
all his purchases ! But Zeldo, who
is a true Genius, had a solution.
A treasure and resale system was
planned... in the manner of
Phantom Hourglass. So Link could
find treasures worth more than
500 Rupees in the advanced
Dungeons of the game !
Enough to allow him to easily
get all these purchases.
Well done Zeldo !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_puzzle_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

     - Eye Puzzle Sketch 1 -

Here is the setup of a
puzzle present in the Earth Temple.
It's a puzzle consisting
of avoiding the gaze of the various
eyes in the room
until reaching the exit door. Link
can shoot the eyes to close them
or push blocks to block their
gaze. Here's the paper version
of the puzzle... Mmmh...
It's indeed very
puzzling ! Let's see the next
painting for the editor version...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_puzzle_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

     - Eye Puzzle Sketch 2 -

Here is now the editor version of the
eye puzzle from the Earth Temple.
This one is clearer and
allows a better visualization
of the path to take.
This puzzle, like the
entire Temple, exist in
playable version...
A comment from the testers
of the time : What a hell !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_screen_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Ingame Screen 1 -

Link traversing the Earth Temple.
This completely finished Dungeon
was beta-tested in 2017.
Here's the assessment from
the testers of the time : it was long,
it was hard, it was the 2017 Zeldo !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_screen_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Ingame Screen 2 -

Link leaving the Tower of Light, the
first Dungeon of the game.
This place was supposed to serve
as a tutorial and allowed to find
the Ocarina, an item leading to
the Tower of Triforce.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.tott.paintings.dev_screen_3",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

        - Ingame Screen 3 -

Link standing before the legendary
Tower of Triforce. The Tower was
supposed to be located in the
celestial islands.
]],
}

