]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.zeldo_wave_1.stop_the_joke",
  text = [[
Oops, looks like I went
a bit too hard :P$0
I'll give you one last chance.
Try to last more than
10 seconds this time...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.zeldo_wave_2.desesperate_move",
  text = [[
So you never give up, huh ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.zeldo_wave_2.end_floor",
  text = [[
You managed to complete
this second Wave of
content ! Well done !
I've barely shown you
the extent of my
unfinished Labors.
We'll meet again !
For a 3rd Wave !
You have my word, little darling.
In the meantime, I'll spend
the end of the year working on
the ZeldoPack...
I plan to optimize many things,
thanks to my recent progress
and DarkDavy15's help.
I hope you enjoyed
exploring this second Wave
dedicated to The 1st Solarus Quest.
It was a first test game,
which I might have released
to the public, but in the end...
Well, like with the first
Wave back then, here's
a modest credit roll for you.
You'll be invited again
to these mysterious rooms
when the 3rd Wave is ready.
Meanwhile, did you manage to 100%
these 2 Waves of The Labors of
Zeldo ? Good luck with that.
See you later !
And don't forget, you're
all beautiful here ! :)
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.zeldo_wave_2.welcome",
  text = [[
Well done, little cutie.
You're still alive, and you've
reached the Hub of Wave 2.
This one is dedicated to The
1st Solarus Quest. It's my
very first Solarus project.
It was a huge test
made when I discovered
the engine in 2015/2016.
Forgotten Legend takes up the lore
from this first draft... So
you might recognize some Zones.
You'll notice pretty quickly that
the Labor Zones in this Wave
can be quite large.
Also, to help you, let me
give you this item : It's
the Magic Mirror ! Take it.
If you find yourself too far
from the start of the Zone,
just take a look at it...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "LABORS.zeldo_wave_2.welcome_2",
  text = [[
This magical artifact should
be very useful to you !
Oh yes, one last thing...
Be careful, I wasn't as
kind as I am now... Although
the Zones were adapted,
some tricks from back then
were kept. Sorry in advance...
or not ! :P
Good luck to you !
I'll see you at the end of this
floor. I believe in you. Have fate.
]],
}

