dialog{
  id = "agahnim.1.escape",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Grrr ! Well done ! Worthy
of the Hero you are !

But I have no intention
of being defeated !

I will return, so take
what this Temple hides, it
will be no use to you !
You will never uncover the secret
of the Tower as long as I am here.
Ah ah ah ah ah !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "agahnim.1.intro",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Well, well, well...
Here is the famous Hero
everyone talks about. Link, right ?
I am Agahnim, Sage
in service of Hyrule, but mostly
in service of its destruction !
You don't need to know more
because your days end
today. En garde !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "agahnim.3.escape",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
$1Argh...$0
Well done...$0
. . .$0
$3However, I have not said
my last word. En garde !$0
Come to me, clones !
Destroy this impudent one !$0
Farewell, Link...$0
Ah ah ah ah ah !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "agahnim.3.intro",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
The view of the Kingdom is
beautiful from here, don't
you think, Link ?
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "agahnim.3.intro_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
For a long time I have served
Hyrule, in the Shadows. Since
forever, the Shadows lived apart.
But now that time is over ! Thanks
to the Tablets, I will finally
uncover the secret of the Tower
and the Triforce will be mine !
So there's only one thing left
to do... Link.
I will annihilate you, right here
and build a new future for Hyrule,
under the Shadows ! Ah ah ah ah !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.1st_time",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Well, well, well, if it isn't Link ! How could you forget me ?
    It's me, the Antiquarian who travels the world in search of new treasures.
    I heard that many treasures were resting in Hyrule, so here I am.
    What ? My usefulness ? Do I really have to remind you of everything ?
    As an Antiquarian, I search for treasures, just like you.
    So, you can show me the treasures you've found on your quest.
    If the item seems interesting to me, I'll buy it from you.
    This will not only allow you to get rid of those treasures
    that you find too cumbersome but also to expand my collection !
    Selling me a treasure also has another advantage :
    every treasure you sell me will be for sale in my unique shop !
    However, I must warn you that I will take 25 percent of
    the profits on each treasure you sell to me; after all, I am a merchant...
    I hope you won't forget this time ! So, do you have a treasure for me ?
    To show me a treasure, assign it to a key and press
    that key in front of me.
    I hope you have some interesting items... I'll give you a good price, I promise...
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.amount_big_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Not bad ! I'll buy this item back from you for $v rupees.
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.amount_bigger_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    But... where did you find this ?
    This is easily worth $v rupees at least !
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.amount_normal_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    A fine piece !
    I'll buy it back from you for $v rupees.
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.amount_small_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    It's not worth more than $v rupees,
    and even that's generous...
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.amount_very_small_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    What's this...
    I'll buy it for $v rupees, but
    only because it's you !
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.cant_resell",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    I can't buy this from you !
    Don't you have anything else
    to show me ?
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.question",
  question = "1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Does this suit you ?
    Yes
    No
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.reflexion",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Hm... let me think...
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.resale_no",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    No ? Then I won't buy it for any more, understand !
    Do you have something else to show me ?
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.resale_yes",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Thank you very much !
    Heh heh heh...
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "antiquarian.welcome",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
    Ah, there you are again ! Do you have a treasure
    you'd like to show me ? I'll give you a good price.
    To show me a treasure, you need to press
    the key to which you assigned it !
  
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "book.tips_rupees",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Having trouble
finding Rupees ?
This Guide is for you !
First and foremost, it's
essential to open all chests
that the World contains...
These can contain
a lot of money, especially in
the Dungeons.
Villages are also
a place where it's easy to
find Rupees.
You can even find Rupees
that respawn endlessly
under the pots.
Finally, it's worth knowing that
Lord Zeldo is a little rascal...

He actually hid
a Silver Rupee in each
of his Labor Zones,
except in the Dungeons,
as those contain secret
rooms.
These are, however, very
well hidden behind
elements of the decor.
But if you find them, you'll
probably have enough
Rupees to buy everything !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "book.tips_shards",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
Having trouble finding
the Remembrance Shards ?
This Guide is for you !
Shards (1) are generally
found in chests, and Stones (5)
are hidden in secret places.
Gems (10), on the other hand,
are dropped by Bosses
located in various Zones.
Crystals (25) are hidden
in the final Zones and
represent a great treasure.
You should also know that,
as usual in Zeldo's Creations,
there is a secret room in
each presented Dungeon.


These rooms don't appear
on the Map but can be deduced
by analyzing the Dungeon's pattern.
You now have all the keys
you need to find these
precious Shards.
Get to work ! (And don't forget
to have fun...)
]],
}

