]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.din_shrine_hint",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Armed with the Titan's Arms and
the Eye of Truth, lift the rocks
and follow the path of shields.
Thus, the path of Strength
will be revealed to you.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.farore_shrine_hint",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Armed with What Always
Comes Back to the Sender,
fill the holes deep in the Forest.
Thus, the path of Courage
will be revealed to you.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.hera_mountain",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
What ?$0
This map seems familiar to you ?$0
...$0
Pure coincidence.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.hero_cave",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Hero's Cave.
This mini dungeon was originally
planned for endgame.
For example, this first room
required a very advanced item
to pass. Which one ?
Try to guess !
This first room is the
only trace of this side dungeon.
Feel free to explore it !
Anyway, you can't go further.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.hero_statue",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Here is a representation of the
Hero of Legend who
once saved Hyrule from the Void.
...$0 He looks a bit like you,
right ?$0 What a funny
coincidence, isn't it ? Heh heh heh
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.lost_woods",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Behind this wall lies
the hidden entrance to the
Forest Village.
The Player was supposed to have
Zelda's Lullaby and play it on
the Triforce to reveal the entrance
That was not done for this
version of The Labors of Zeldo.
Find the entrance elsewhere !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.nayru_shrine_hint",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Equipped with Flippers and a Source
of Fire, find the hidden water
whirlpool in the Plains.
Thus, the path of Wisdom
will be revealed to you.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.power_temple_hint_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Secrets can be
cunningly hidden
behind scenery elements.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.power_temple_hint_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Not all holes
necessarily lead to failure.
Make the right choice.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.power_temple_hint_3",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Walking on the right edges
of the walls and dodging holes ?
It's legal for 2015 Zeldo.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.to_castle_passage",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
In this direction lies
a very mysterious cave...
It has a specific purpose and
is also present in
Zelda Forgotten Legend.
What is the purpose of this cave ?
Good question...$0
Wait for the release of Zelda
Forgotten Legend to find out.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.to_castle_passage_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
In this direction lies
a very mysterious cave...
It has a specific purpose and
is also present in
Zelda Forgotten Legend.
What is the purpose of this cave ?
Good question...$0
Wait for the release of Zelda
Forgotten Legend to find out.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.triforce_shrine_hint",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
When the Goddess Pendants
are found, the Path to the
Sacred Triangles will be revealed.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.water_temple_hint_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
When the statues cover
the water outlets, the torches
will light up.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.water_temple_hint_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Returning to rooms
already visited, with new
equipment, can open new
exploration possibilities.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.water_temple_hint_3",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Strike your sword against cracks
and listen carefully... only the
real ones make special sounds.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.water_temple_hint_4",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Absolutely nothing this way.
So why this alcove ?$0
Even Zeldo doesn't remember.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.1st_solarus_quest.water_temple_secret_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Due to a design from 2015
and rules not yet fully
established, this Dungeon
has 2 secret rooms.
To stay compatible with
the spirit of Zeldo's Labors,
the rewards from these rooms
can be obtained only once,
so you don't need to find
both rooms for 100%.
But you can look for both
just for fun.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_blue_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Blue
Galleries Room !

Here you are in the Sound Test
Chamber... interact with the
Sopranotes to listen to the various
musics that were planned in the
final project... Enjoy your
listening, dear Guest.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_blue_room_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Blue
Galleries Room !

You will find here exclusive
development notes, sketches,
or screens !
Inspect the paintings to
learn more... happy
reading, dear Guest.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_green_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Green
Galleries Room !

The portal at the back of the room
will take you to the Dungeon Room
upon request.
A Room in which you will be
transported into the settings
of the various planned Dungeons.
In this magical Room, activate
the switches to switch from one
Dungeon to another...
There is also an informative plaque
on each Dungeon presented.
Enjoy, dear Guest.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_green_room_2",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Green Gallery Room
of this Wave !

Activate the crystal at the back
of the room to access the
Developer's Commentary.
A hidden link will open, leading
you to a private YouTube playlist.
Enjoy the show, dear Guest.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_purple_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Purple Gallery Room
of this Wave !

You must have worked hard
to find the Key
to this secret Room...
So here is a reward worthy
of being so well hidden :
Activate the crystal at the back
of the room to access a secret
download link.
It's a prototype of
The 1st Solarus Quest from 2016,
fully playable !
The game is in .exe format though,
sorry to those playing
on their favorite calculator...
The game is uncalibrated,
Zeldo wanted to keep the
experience intact. So it'll be
unplayable !
Are you ready to face
2016's Zeldo, aka oly64 ?
Have fun, dear Guest.
By the way, the project is hosted
on Mediafire, since Google Drive
refused... Sorry.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_red_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Red
Galleries Room !

You will find here exclusive
development notes, sketches,
or screens !
Inspect the paintings to
learn more... happy
reading, dear Guest.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_rules",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

  - Zeldo's Galleries Corridor -

Access exclusive development
content here, provided by
Zeldo himself.
Find the various Gallery Keys. Each
one will give you access to
a new section.
What lies behind these doors ?
It's up to you to find out...
Happy exploring !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.gallery_useless_room",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Welcome to the Useless
Galleries Room !

This room serves no purpose.$0
No kidding.$0 It's just a
transition to the next room.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.labors_end_wave",
  skip = "all",
  text = [[
You have reached the end of
this Wave of content.
Congratulations !
Take the teleporter on the right
if you want to watch the Credits
and view your Wave Statistics.
Please note that checking your
Statistics at least once is
required to validate your Rank.
The adventure is, of course,
not over yet. Head North
for the next Wave !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.labors_rules",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

    - Zeldo's Labors Corridor -

Explore the various Labors of
Zeldo available and win
the Trophies to progress.
New Zones will unlock gradually
as you win Trophies.

Feel free to observe the frames
behind the portals for more
informations about the Zones.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.shop_rules",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[

           - The Shops -

Use the resources collected
in Zeldo's Labors to
buy useful items.
The Rupees will allow you
to obtain various upgrades that
will help you in the Zones.
The Remembrance Shards will
allow you to acquire the
Gallery Keys.
Warning : The various items
obtained here are only usable
for the current floor.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_1_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 1 :
Light Temple

The very first Dungeon that Link
had to traverse. He found the
Ocarina there, which was supposed
to allow him to bypass the game's
introduction. He was then free
to explore the Kingdom of Hyrule
almost in its entirety.
This Dungeon was planned as
the game's tutorial and a light
version of the future obstacles
Link would have faced in his
adventure. A playable prototype
of the Dungeon exists...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_2_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 2 :
Earth Temple

This Dungeon located after the
Lost Woods was supposed to be
Link's first real challenge.
The difficulty was increased
to show that the tutorial stage
was over. He was supposed to
obtain the Bow and use it to find
4 green statues hidden in the
Dungeon. This Dungeon was
finalized in a playable prototype
version and could even be
beta tested by a few chosen ones...
Adenothe, Nirelia, and Renkineko
could tell you more...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_3_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 3 :
Fire Temple

A Dungeon at a fairly
advanced stage. You could play
it in one of my Labors.
So there's not much
else to say... the second
half of the Dungeon was never
finished even though the ideas
for its design remain
in my mind.
So I hope this first
half was enjoyable enough for you.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_4_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 4 :
Water Temple

Probably my greatest
Dungeon design achievement.
Did you hate it ? Amateurs !
Know that this Temple has
an alpha version that was even
more challenging and puzzling...
Perhaps I'll offer it to you
one day...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_5_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 5 :
Desert Temple

Probably the least advanced
Dungeon on the entire list.
Link was supposed to obtain the
Hammer there.
The rest ? I don't really know.
The Dungeon was supposed to
feature many traps and
mechanisms like an ancient
pyramid but I never did anything
concrete about it. Even the
decoration of the room you
see right now was not at all final.
Maybe one day I'll be motivated
enough to create a pyramid
worthy of its name !
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_6_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 6 :
Ice Temple

A Dungeon located in the second
half of the game for Link. He was
supposed to obtain the Ice Rod.
If you want to imagine what this
Dungeon could have looked like,
I refer you to the Ice Palace in
Zeldo's Challenge Chapter 2.
It's a slightly mini version of the
planned Dungeon.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_7_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 7 :
Wind Temple

A Dungeon in a theme
that I really like : the Sky !
So I was very motivated to do it.
Unfortunately, the planned
item for the Dungeon, which was
the Feather, caused me a lot
of problems... Having reused the
one from A Link to the Dream,
I ran into many bugs...
So I couldn't get very far
in the development of this Dungeon
even though all its aesthetics
were final. Since then, I haven't
used any items from ALTTD...
Oh wait...
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_8_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 8 :
Shadow Temple

And no, this is not the
Ancient Tomb presented
in my Labors.
This was only the Mini-Dungeon
leading to this much tougher Temple.
The Shadow Temple was
therefore the last logical Dungeon
before the Tower. Link found
the Mirror Shield there which
allowed him to become very
resistant to any projectile.
The Boss of this place was
supposed to be Agahnim,
encountered for a fairly similar
battle to the one presented in
my Labors. This Dungeon was
supposed to rely heavily
on its atmosphere...$0
A heavy...$0
oppressive...$0
An atmosphere where
a more horrific atmosphere...$0
Wouldn't it be an opportunity to...$0
Redeem myself ? $0

        $1I T    A R R I V E S
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.dungeon_9_info",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
Level 9 :
Tower of the triforce

The last Dungeon. The climax.
My greatest creation.
The ABSOLUTE Dungeon.
8 floors. Each one a revision of
each of the 8 Dungeons
traversed.
Then the Real Dungeon begins
with unique mechanics. Every
item used.
A density never seen before.
An obstacle course.
The Ultimate Test for Link.
My idea was for the player
to spend hours there... yes,
I was completely crazy.
But that was the Zeldo of 2017.
Not having finished this Tower
remains my greatest regret...
Some floors are finished and
playable. But they contain all
the WORST of what I could create.
Link will never be ready. Never
to climb the Triforce Tower. The
Triforce will remain at its peak.
Forever.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.fire_temple_hint_1",
  skip = "current",
  text = [[
The 4 torches hidden in
the darkness must all be
lit within the allotted time.
]],
}

dialog{
  id = "ts.labors.tott.fire_temple_hint_2",
